  <refnamediv>
    <refname>lowdisc_primes10000</refname><refpurpose>Returns a matrix containing the 10000 first primes.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>



<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Calling Sequence</title>
   <synopsis>
   m = lowdisc_primes10000 ( )
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>m:</term>
      <listitem><para> a 1x10000 matrix of doubles</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
This function allows to update the table of
primes associated to the "-primeslist" option, so that
we can use a low discrepancy sequence in higher dimensions.
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
prarray = lowdisc_primes10000 ( );
size(prarray)

lds = lowdisc_new("faure");
prarray = lowdisc_primes10000 ( );
lds = lowdisc_configure(lds,"-primeslist",prarray);
lds = lowdisc_configure(lds,"-dimension",1500);
[lds,next] = lowdisc_next ( lds );
next
lds = lowdisc_destroy(lds);

   ]]></programlisting>
</refsection>

